This product includes software adapted from third-party projects:

* Neon (https://github.com/neondatabase/neon), Apache License 2.0,
  Copyright (c) Neon, Inc.
  The quorum tail backend's consensus core — the acceptor state machine
  (voting, term history, divergence-point computation and truncation, the
  persist-before-respond discipline) and the proposer's election / donor
  selection / recovery / quorum-commit rules — is adapted from Neon's
  safekeeper (safekeeper/src/safekeeper.rs, safekeeper/src/control_file.rs)
  and its WAL proposer (pgxn/neon/walproposer.c), substantially modified
  for icegres's generic tail log (Postgres WAL framing replaced by
  icegres's crc-framed record log; no tenants/timelines/membership
  generations). The adapted files carry per-file attribution headers:
  icegres/src/quorum/proto.rs, icegres/src/quorum/acceptor.rs,
  icegres/src/quorum/proposer.rs.
